Italy ' s SanPaolo plans share buyback . The board of Italian banking group San Paolo said it intended to ask shareholders for authorisation to buy and allocate its own shares and to create a reserve of 200 billion lire for the proposed share buyback . A San Paolo statement said the shares from the proposed buyback would serve two purposes , firstly for stock market operations within the framework of its privatisation . Secondly the buyback would allow the creation of a pool of shares to be used as a form of incentive in the eventual allocation of stock to employees of the bank . - - Milan bureau + 392 66129507 
